### Step 0.1 — Refactor `ModelRegistry` (Kill the 60+ `@Value` Fields)

**Why**: The current `ModelRegistry.java` has 60+ individual `@Value` annotations. This is unmaintainable. Spring Boot has `@ConfigurationProperties` for exactly this.

**What to do**:

1. Create a new file `knowledge-bot-ai/src/main/java/com/knowledgebot/ai/model/ModelRoutingProperties.java`:

```java
package com.knowledgebot.ai.model;

import org.springframework.boot.context.properties.ConfigurationProperties;
import java.util.Map;

/**
 * WHY: Instead of 60+ @Value fields, we bind the entire YAML section
 * "knowledge-bot.model-routing" to this single POJO.
 *
 * HOW IT WORKS: Spring Boot reads the YAML and automatically maps
 * nested keys to these fields. For example:
 *   knowledge-bot.model-routing.default-model-key: local-fast
 * gets mapped to this.defaultModelKey
 */
@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = "knowledge-bot.model-routing")
public class ModelRoutingProperties {

    private String defaultModelKey = "local-fast";
    private String fallbackModelKey = "local-fallback";
    private boolean autoFailover = true;
    private long requestTimeoutMs = 30000;

    /**
     * Each entry in the map represents one model configuration.
     * In YAML it looks like:
     *   knowledge-bot.model-routing.models:
     *     local-fast:
     *       provider: OLLAMA
     *       model: llama3.2:3b
     *       min-complexity: SIMPLE
     *       ...
     */
    private Map<String, ModelConfig> models;

    // Getters + Setters for all fields (generate with IDE)

    public static class ModelConfig {
        private String provider = "OLLAMA";
        private String model;
        private String minComplexity = "SIMPLE";
        private String maxComplexity = "MODERATE";
        private double cost = 0.0;
        private double maxTokens = 32000;
        private int contextWindow = 8192;
        private int promptBudget = 4000;
        private String purpose = "";
        // Getters + Setters
    }
}
```

