## Phase 1: The Agentic Tool-Calling Loop

> **Goal**: This is THE most important phase. After this, the LLM can autonomously decide to read files, write code, run commands — without the user typing separate CLI commands.

### What Is an Agentic Loop?

Currently: User types `generate code for X` → bot calls LLM once → returns text.

After this phase: User types `Build a REST API` → bot calls LLM → LLM decides to:
1. First call `list_directory` to see the project structure
2. Then call `read_file` to read pom.xml
3. Then call `write_file` to create Controller.java
4. Then call `write_file` to create Service.java
5. Then call `run_command` to run `mvn compile`
6. See an error → call `read_file` on the failed file
7. Call `write_file` to fix it
8. Call `run_command` again → success

The LLM **decides** which tools to call. The code just provides the tools and the loop.

### Step 1.1 — Define Tool Interfaces with Spring AI `@Tool`

Spring AI 2.0 has `@Tool` annotation. Create these tool classes:

**File**: `knowledge-bot-ai/src/main/java/com/knowledgebot/ai/tools/FileReadTool.java`

```java
package com.knowledgebot.ai.tools;

import com.knowledgebot.ai.model.WorkspaceManager;
import org.springframework.ai.tool.annotation.Tool;
import org.springframework.ai.tool.annotation.ToolParam;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Path;

/**
 * WHY: The LLM needs to read files in the workspace to understand the project.
 *
 * HOW: When the LLM decides it needs to read a file, Spring AI automatically
 * calls this method, passes the arguments the LLM chose, and returns the
 * result back to the LLM as a tool response.
 */
@Component
public class FileReadTool {

    private final WorkspaceManager workspaceManager;

    public FileReadTool(WorkspaceManager workspaceManager) {
        this.workspaceManager = workspaceManager;
    }

    @Tool(description = "Read the contents of a file in the workspace. Use this to understand existing code, configs, or any file before making changes.")
    public String readFile(
        @ToolParam(description = "Relative path to the file within the workspace, e.g. 'src/main/java/App.java'") String path
    ) {
        try {
            Path fullPath = workspaceManager.resolve(path);

            // SECURITY: Make sure the path is inside the workspace
            if (!fullPath.startsWith(workspaceManager.getActiveWorkspace())) {
                return "ERROR: Path is outside the workspace boundary. Access denied.";
            }

            if (!Files.exists(fullPath)) {
                return "ERROR: File not found: " + path;
            }

            String content = Files.readString(fullPath);
            // Truncate if too large (prevent context overflow)
            if (content.length() > 50000) {
                return content.substring(0, 50000) + "\n\n... [TRUNCATED - file too large, showing first 50000 chars]";
            }
            return content;
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return "ERROR reading file: " + e.getMessage();
        }
    }
}
```

