## Phase 8: Startup Flow & Folder Permission

> **Goal**: When the app starts, force the user to pick a workspace folder before anything else works.

### Step 8.1 — Backend: Enforce Workspace Selection

Add a Spring Web filter that blocks ALL API calls except workspace-related ones if no workspace is attached:

```java
@Component
public class WorkspaceRequiredFilter implements WebFilter {

    private final WorkspaceManager workspaceManager;

    private static final Set<String> EXEMPT_PATHS = Set.of(
        "/api/v1/workspace",
        "/api/v1/health",
        "/api/v1/settings"
    );

    @Override
    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {
        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();

        if (EXEMPT_PATHS.stream().anyMatch(path::startsWith)) {
            return chain.filter(exchange);
        }

        if (!workspaceManager.isWorkspaceAttached()) {
            exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.PRECONDITION_REQUIRED);
            // Return JSON error telling the UI to show the folder picker
            return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(
                Mono.just(exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory()
                    .wrap("{\"error\":\"WORKSPACE_REQUIRED\"}".getBytes()))
            );
        }

        return chain.filter(exchange);
    }
}
```

