## Phase 10: IDE Integration

> **Goal**: When the bot creates or modifies a file, the user can click to open it in VS Code or IntelliJ.

### Step 10.1 — Backend: IDE Launcher Endpoint

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/ide")
public class IdeController {

    @PostMapping("/open")
    public ResponseEntity<String> openInIde(
        @RequestBody Map<String, String> request
    ) {
        String filePath = request.get("path");
        String editor = request.getOrDefault("editor", "vscode");

        Path fullPath = workspaceManager.resolve(filePath);

        try {
            ProcessBuilder pb;
            if ("intellij".equals(editor)) {
                // IntelliJ IDEA command line
                pb = new ProcessBuilder("idea", fullPath.toString());
            } else {
                // VS Code command line
                pb = new ProcessBuilder("code", fullPath.toString());
            }
            pb.start();
            return ResponseEntity.ok("Opened in " + editor);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            return ResponseEntity.status(500)
                .body("Failed to open editor: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }
}
```

