## Final Notes for Junior Developers

> [!TIP]
> 1. **Build each phase completely before moving to the next**. Each phase has a checkpoint — verify it works before continuing.
> 2. **Write tests as you go**. Every new service should have at least 3 unit tests.
> 3. **Start Ollama first**: Run `ollama serve` and `ollama pull llama3.2:3b` before starting the app.
> 4. **Start Docker**: Run `docker compose up -d` for PostgreSQL before the app.
> 5. **Create `.env` from `.env.example`** and set your database credentials.
> 6. **The most critical files** are marked with ⭐. If you get stuck, focus on those first.
> 7. **Spring AI 2.0 documentation**: https://docs.spring.io/spring-ai/reference/ — read the "Tool Calling" section thoroughly.
> 8. **Don't skip Phase 0**. Cleanup first, build second.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Security Reminders**:
> - NEVER allow the agent to access files outside the workspace folder
> - ALWAYS validate paths with `WorkspaceManager.validatePathInWorkspace()`
> - ALWAYS block dangerous shell commands in `CommandExecutionTool`
> - NEVER expose API endpoints without workspace validation
> - ALWAYS use environment variables for secrets, never hardcode them
